{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01CfWsYwjnXf1PqBbnjoTNLn","type":"tool_result","content":"1\tname: vllm-test-audit-eval\n2\tdescription: F1 and token efficiency evaluation of vllm-test-audit\n3\t\n4\t# Empty because the audit is invoked via Agent tool (coordinator-agent),\n5\t# not a slash command. When empty, execute.py sends the arguments as a\n6\t# plain natural-language prompt.\n7\tskill: \"\"\n8\t\n9\toptimize:\n10\t  target: audit-contract\n11\t\n12\texecution:\n13\t  mode: case\n14\t  arguments: >-\n15\t    Use the coordinator agent (subagent_type: vllm-test-audit:coordinator-agent)\n16\t    to run the full audit pipeline on {directory}. Run in FOREGROUND\n17\t    (run_in_background: false) and wait for completion. The agent writes\n18\t    audit-cc.json, audit-not-cc.json, and review-cc.json to the cwd.\n19\t  timeout: 3600\n20\t  max_budget_usd: 5.00\n21\t\n22\trunner:\n23\t  type: claude-code\n24\t  effort: high\n25\t  plugin_dirs:\n26\t    - /home/devuser/projects/ai-marketplace\n27\t\n28\tpermissions:\n29\t  allow:\n30\t    - \"Read\"\n31\t    - \"Edit\"\n32\t    - \"Write\"\n33\t    - \"Bash(*)\"\n34\t    - \"Agent(*)\"\n35\t    - \"Skill(*)\"\n36\t    - \"WebFetch(*)\"\n37\t    - \"WebSearch(*)\"\n38\t    - \"SendMessage(*)\"\n39\t    - \"TaskCreate\"\n40\t    - \"TaskUpdate\"\n41\t    - \"TaskList\"\n42\t    - \"TaskGet\"\n43\t    - \"mcp__*\"\n44\t\n45\thooks:\n46\t  before_each:\n47\t    - command: >-\n48\t        python3 \"$(dirname \"$AGENT_EVAL_CONFIG\")/scripts/setup_workspace.py\"\n49\t      description: \"Symlink vLLM tests, add additionalDirectories, trust workspace\"\n50\t\n51\tmodels:\n52\t  skill: opus\n53\t\n54\ttraces:\n55\t  stdout: true\n56\t  stderr: true\n57\t  events: true\n58\t  metrics: true\n59\t\n60\tdataset:\n61\t  path: cases\n62\t  schema: |\n63\t    Each case has a 'directory' field pointing to a vLLM test directory to audit.\n64\t\n65\toutputs:\n66\t  - path: audit-cc.json\n67\t    schema: \"Phase 1 CC candidates with classification and c1/c2/c3 criteria\"\n68\t  - path: audit-not-cc.json\n69\t    schema: \"Phase 1 non-CC candidates\"\n70\t  - path: review-cc.json\n71\t    schema: \"Phase 2 reviewed candidates with AGREE/RECLASSIFY verdicts\"\n72\t\n73\tjudges:\n74\t  - name: f1_score\n75\t    module: judges.f1_score\n76\t    function: judge\n77\t    description: \"F1 score against expert-verified golden.csv\"\n78\t    score_range: [0, 1]\n79\t    arguments:\n80\t      golden_path: golden.csv\n81\t\n82\t  - name: cost_per_test\n83\t    module: judges.cost_per_test\n84\t    function: judge\n85\t    description: \"Token cost efficiency normalized by tests analyzed\"\n86\t    score_range: [0, 1]\n87\t    arguments:\n88\t      target_cost_per_test: 0.50\n89\t\n90\t  - name: phase_delta\n91\t    module: judges.phase_delta\n92\t    function: judge\n93\t    description: \"Phase 2 marginal F1 contribution (positive = helpful)\"\n94\t    score_range: [-1, 1]\n95\t    arguments:\n96\t      golden_path: golden.csv\n97\t\n98\tthresholds:\n99\t  f1_score:\n100\t    min_mean: 0.90\n101\t  cost_per_test:\n102\t    min_mean: 0.80\n103\t\n104\treward:\n105\t  formula: weighted\n106\t  weights:\n107\t    f1_score: 0.7\n108\t    cost_per_test: 0.3\n109\t  score_range: [0, 1]\n110\t  raw: [f1_score, cost_per_test]\n111\t  gate: false\n112\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"603f2b8b-1633-4397-a4a3-f9f63565a548","uuid":"b3434e2d-02f1-4a73-bc8d-cc9623212edd","timestamp":"2026-07-13T16:44:40.111Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/devuser/projects/vllm-eval-harness/eval.yaml","content":"name: vllm-test-audit-eval\ndescription: F1 and token efficiency evaluation of vllm-test-audit\n\n# Empty because the audit is invoked via Agent tool (coordinator-agent),\n# not a slash command. When empty, execute.py sends the arguments as a\n# plain natural-language prompt.\nskill: \"\"\n\noptimize:\n  target: audit-contract\n\nexecution:\n  mode: case\n  arguments: >-\n    Use the coordinator agent (subagent_type: vllm-test-audit:coordinator-agent)\n    to run the full audit pipeline on {directory}. Run in FOREGROUND\n    (run_in_background: false) and wait for completion. The agent writes\n    audit-cc.json, audit-not-cc.json, and review-cc.json to the cwd.\n  timeout: 3600\n  max_budget_usd: 5.00\n\nrunner:\n  type: claude-code\n  effort: high\n  plugin_dirs:\n    - /home/devuser/projects/ai-marketplace\n\npermissions:\n  allow:\n    - \"Read\"\n    - \"Edit\"\n    - \"Write\"\n    - \"Bash(*)\"\n    - \"Agent(*)\"\n    - \"Skill(*)\"\n    - \"WebFetch(*)\"\n    - \"WebSearch(*)\"\n    - \"SendMessage(*)\"\n    - \"TaskCreate\"\n    - \"TaskUpdate\"\n    - \"TaskList\"\n    - \"TaskGet\"\n    - \"mcp__*\"\n\nhooks:\n  before_each:\n    - command: >-\n        python3 \"$(dirname \"$AGENT_EVAL_CONFIG\")/scripts/setup_workspace.py\"\n      description: \"Symlink vLLM tests, add additionalDirectories, trust workspace\"\n\nmodels:\n  skill: opus\n\ntraces:\n  stdout: true\n  stderr: true\n  events: true\n  metrics: true\n\ndataset:\n  path: cases\n  schema: |\n    Each case has a 'directory' field pointing to a vLLM test directory to audit.\n\noutputs:\n  - path: audit-cc.json\n    schema: \"Phase 1 CC candidates with classification and c1/c2/c3 criteria\"\n  - path: audit-not-cc.json\n    schema: \"Phase 1 non-CC candidates\"\n  - path: review-cc.json\n    schema: \"Phase 2 reviewed candidates with AGREE/RECLASSIFY verdicts\"\n\njudges:\n  - name: f1_score\n    module: judges.f1_score\n    function: judge\n    description: \"F1 score against expert-verified golden.csv\"\n    score_range: [0, 1]\n    arguments:\n      golden_path: golden.csv\n\n  - name: cost_per_test\n    module: judges.cost_per_test\n    function: judge\n    description: \"Token cost efficiency normalized by tests analyzed\"\n    score_range: [0, 1]\n    arguments:\n      target_cost_per_test: 0.50\n\n  - name: phase_delta\n    module: judges.phase_delta\n    function: judge\n    description: \"Phase 2 marginal F1 contribution (positive = helpful)\"\n    score_range: [-1, 1]\n    arguments:\n      golden_path: golden.csv\n\nthresholds:\n  f1_score:\n    min_mean: 0.90\n  cost_per_test:\n    min_mean: 0.80\n\nreward:\n  formula: weighted\n  weights:\n    f1_score: 0.7\n    cost_per_test: 0.3\n  score_range: [0, 1]\n  raw: [f1_score, cost_per_test]\n  gate: false\n","numLines":112,"startLine":1,"totalLines":112}}}
