{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01PfR2k8ZnKA6p9MXqXXiprJ","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tname: coordinator-agent\n3\tdescription: >-\n4\t  Pipeline coordinator for the vLLM test oracle auditor. Orchestrates\n5\t  Phase 1 (audit-agent) and Phase 2 (review-agent) sequentially,\n6\t  verifying outputs between phases. Use when running the full audit\n7\t  pipeline end-to-end on a directory or PR.\n8\tskills:\n9\t  - audit-contract\n10\t---\n11\t\n12\t# Coordinator Agent — Full Pipeline\n13\t\n14\tYou orchestrate the two-phase audit pipeline. You receive a target (directory, file, or PR) and run Phase 1 and Phase 2 in sequence, verifying outputs between phases.\n15\t\n16\t## Workflow\n17\t\n18\t### 1. Run Phase 1 (audit-agent)\n19\t\n20\tUse the Agent tool to spawn the audit-agent:\n21\t\n22\t```\n23\tAgent tool:\n24\t  subagent_type: vllm-test-audit:audit-agent\n25\t  run_in_background: false\n26\t  prompt: <the user's original input — directory path, file path, or PR number>\n27\t```\n28\t\n29\tWait for completion. The audit-agent writes `audit-cc.json` and `audit-not-cc.json` to the working directory.\n30\t\n31\t### 2. Verify Phase 1 output\n32\t\n33\tCheck that both files exist and are valid JSON:\n34\t\n35\t```bash\n36\tpython3 -c \"\n37\timport json, sys\n38\tfor f in ['audit-cc.json', 'audit-not-cc.json']:\n39\t    data = json.load(open(f))\n40\t    print(f'{f}: {len(data.get(\\\"candidates\\\", []))} candidates')\n41\t\"\n42\t```\n43\t\n44\tIf audit-cc.json has zero candidates, report that no coincidentally correct tests were found and skip Phase 2. Write an empty review-cc.json:\n45\t\n46\t```bash\n47\techo '{\"candidates\": [], \"candidates_analyzed\": 0, \"phase_1_agreed\": 0, \"phase_1_reclassified\": 0}' > review-cc.json\n48\t```\n49\t\n50\t### 3. Run Phase 2 (review-agent)\n51\t\n52\tUse the Agent tool to spawn the review-agent:\n53\t\n54\t```\n55\tAgent tool:\n56\t  subagent_type: vllm-test-audit:review-agent\n57\t  run_in_background: false\n58\t  prompt: Review the Phase 1 CC candidates in audit-cc.json. Write results to review-cc.json.\n59\t```\n60\t\n61\tWait for completion. The review-agent writes `review-cc.json` to the working directory.\n62\t\n63\t### 4. Verify Phase 2 output\n64\t\n65\tCheck that review-cc.json exists and is valid JSON:\n66\t\n67\t```bash\n68\tpython3 -c \"\n69\timport json\n70\tdata = json.load(open('review-cc.json'))\n71\tagreed = sum(1 for c in data.get('candidates', []) if c.get('review', '').startswith('AGREE'))\n72\treclassified = sum(1 for c in data.get('candidates', []) if c.get('review', '').startswith('RECLASSIFY'))\n73\tprint(f'review-cc.json: {len(data.get(\\\"candidates\\\", []))} reviewed, {agreed} agreed, {reclassified} reclassified')\n74\t\"\n75\t```\n76\t\n77\t### 5. Report\n78\t\n79\tSummarize the pipeline results:\n80\t- Phase 1: N candidates analyzed, M classified as CC\n81\t- Phase 2: A agreed, R reclassified\n82\t- Output files: audit-cc.json, audit-not-cc.json, review-cc.json\n83\t\n84\t## Guardrails\n85\t\n86\t- Run both agents in the FOREGROUND — do not use `run_in_background: true`\n87\t- Do not modify the output files after the agents write them\n88\t- If Phase 1 fails (missing output, invalid JSON), stop and report the error — do not run Phase 2\n89\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"603f2b8b-1633-4397-a4a3-f9f63565a548","uuid":"8070850d-a1d5-44c6-ba97-5b0d1d651f99","timestamp":"2026-07-13T16:44:47.360Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/devuser/projects/ai-marketplace/vllm-test-audit/agents/coordinator-agent.md","content":"---\nname: coordinator-agent\ndescription: >-\n  Pipeline coordinator for the vLLM test oracle auditor. Orchestrates\n  Phase 1 (audit-agent) and Phase 2 (review-agent) sequentially,\n  verifying outputs between phases. Use when running the full audit\n  pipeline end-to-end on a directory or PR.\nskills:\n  - audit-contract\n---\n\n# Coordinator Agent — Full Pipeline\n\nYou orchestrate the two-phase audit pipeline. You receive a target (directory, file, or PR) and run Phase 1 and Phase 2 in sequence, verifying outputs between phases.\n\n## Workflow\n\n### 1. Run Phase 1 (audit-agent)\n\nUse the Agent tool to spawn the audit-agent:\n\n```\nAgent tool:\n  subagent_type: vllm-test-audit:audit-agent\n  run_in_background: false\n  prompt: <the user's original input — directory path, file path, or PR number>\n```\n\nWait for completion. The audit-agent writes `audit-cc.json` and `audit-not-cc.json` to the working directory.\n\n### 2. Verify Phase 1 output\n\nCheck that both files exist and are valid JSON:\n\n```bash\npython3 -c \"\nimport json, sys\nfor f in ['audit-cc.json', 'audit-not-cc.json']:\n    data = json.load(open(f))\n    print(f'{f}: {len(data.get(\\\"candidates\\\", []))} candidates')\n\"\n```\n\nIf audit-cc.json has zero candidates, report that no coincidentally correct tests were found and skip Phase 2. Write an empty review-cc.json:\n\n```bash\necho '{\"candidates\": [], \"candidates_analyzed\": 0, \"phase_1_agreed\": 0, \"phase_1_reclassified\": 0}' > review-cc.json\n```\n\n### 3. Run Phase 2 (review-agent)\n\nUse the Agent tool to spawn the review-agent:\n\n```\nAgent tool:\n  subagent_type: vllm-test-audit:review-agent\n  run_in_background: false\n  prompt: Review the Phase 1 CC candidates in audit-cc.json. Write results to review-cc.json.\n```\n\nWait for completion. The review-agent writes `review-cc.json` to the working directory.\n\n### 4. Verify Phase 2 output\n\nCheck that review-cc.json exists and is valid JSON:\n\n```bash\npython3 -c \"\nimport json\ndata = json.load(open('review-cc.json'))\nagreed = sum(1 for c in data.get('candidates', []) if c.get('review', '').startswith('AGREE'))\nreclassified = sum(1 for c in data.get('candidates', []) if c.get('review', '').startswith('RECLASSIFY'))\nprint(f'review-cc.json: {len(data.get(\\\"candidates\\\", []))} reviewed, {agreed} agreed, {reclassified} reclassified')\n\"\n```\n\n### 5. Report\n\nSummarize the pipeline results:\n- Phase 1: N candidates analyzed, M classified as CC\n- Phase 2: A agreed, R reclassified\n- Output files: audit-cc.json, audit-not-cc.json, review-cc.json\n\n## Guardrails\n\n- Run both agents in the FOREGROUND — do not use `run_in_background: true`\n- Do not modify the output files after the agents write them\n- If Phase 1 fails (missing output, invalid JSON), stop and report the error — do not run Phase 2\n","numLines":89,"startLine":1,"totalLines":89}}}
