{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_011hBZhrPKXPon6akLXFWMMz","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Worked Examples\n2\t\n3\tTwo examples showing the full Phase 1 → Phase 2 pipeline: one COINCIDENTALLY_CORRECT, one STRONG_CONTRACT.\n4\t\n5\t## Example 1: test_cascade_attention (COINCIDENTALLY_CORRECT)\n6\t\n7\tFrom `tests/v1/e2e/general/test_cascade_attention.py`:\n8\t\n9\t```python\n10\tsingle_prompt = [example_system_message + prompt]\n11\tresponses = llm.generate(single_prompt, sampling_params)  # temp=0.0\n12\tref_output = responses[0].outputs[0].text\n13\t\n14\t# (Probably) Use cascade attention.\n15\tprompts = [example_system_message + prompt] * 64\n16\tresponses = llm.generate(prompts, sampling_params)\n17\tfor response in responses:\n18\t    assert response.outputs[0].text == ref_output  # EXACT string match\n19\t```\n20\t\n21\t**Why it's coincidentally correct:** Compares batch=1 vs batch=64 via exact string equality without `VLLM_BATCH_INVARIANT`. No strong contract (Not Strong #6). PyTorch issue 182700 showed this breaks.\n22\t\n23\t### Phase 1 output\n24\t\n25\t```python\n26\timport sys\n27\tsys.path.insert(0, \"${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/scripts\")\n28\tfrom output_object import AuditCandidate, AuditReport\n29\t\n30\treport = AuditReport(\n31\t    test_files_in_scope=1,\n32\t    candidates_analyzed=1,\n33\t    candidates=[\n34\t        AuditCandidate(\n35\t            candidate=\"test_cascade_attention\",\n36\t            file=\"tests/v1/e2e/general/test_cascade_attention.py\",\n37\t            line=43,\n38\t            comparison=\"batch=1 vs batch=64\",\n39\t            oracle=\"exact text equality (assert .text ==)\",\n40\t            helper=\"direct assertion\",\n41\t            batch_invariant_enabled=False,\n42\t            code_path_verified=False,\n43\t            fixtures=\"@create_new_process_for_each_test()\",\n44\t            c1_weak_oracle=\"yes — exact string == on generated text\",\n45\t            c2_r